descripción:
River Global is an international trade and marketing consulting company with presence in Sao Paulo, Bogota and Santiago. We provide our clients with all support needed to expand or establish their businesses in South America, specialized in market access, regulatory affairs, trade promotion and marketing, especially in the food industry. 


The junior consultant is responsible to develop routines in the areas of trade promotion, investment promotion, marketing and work with concrete goals and challenges. River Global Junior Program offers the opportunity to participate in meetings, attend seminars and speeches of international caliber.  

Activities: 

Assist in trade development in Chile for Agribusiness, especially in the seafood market 
Development of new contacts in Chile for River Global’s clients 
Maintain a relationship with seafood processing industry, importers, distributors and food and beverage associations in Chile 
Development of new business opportunities for River Global’s clients 
Work on general regulatory and technical aspects of the food and beverage industries, including dairy, meat, seafood, among others; 
Schedule meetings importers, distributors; 
Market Research in Chile for food and beverage  

Training  

The first month of the program is taken up by training. During this period, the junior consultant will learn about the company and its services; receive lectures from Account Managers and learn more about regulatory affairs, marketing, sales techniques, cross cultural negotiations, business match-making, office routine operations and communication. 

Requisites 

Be enrolled in University (Food Engineering, agribusiness, administration or related fields) or have a University degree; 
Availability to work 30 hours a week during commercial hours; 
Capacity of working 100% from home
Advanced English; 
Strong communication skills; 
Strong knowledge of Office Tools. 

Salary: 400 USD (w/ all included)
